---
import { EVENT_DURATION } from '~/config';
---

<section id="about" class="section about" data-scene="world">
  <div class="scrim">
    <p class="kicker">01 — The Premise</p>
    <h2 class="display-lg" data-split>
      Software is easy.<br />Ship something <span class="accent">physical.</span>
    </h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p class="lede" data-reveal>
        Most hackathons end with a demo video and a Devpost link. This one ends with an object on a
        table — soldered, wired, humming — that didn't exist {EVENT_DURATION} earlier.
      </p>
      <div class="about-cols" data-reveal>
        <p>
          We hand you the parts: microcontrollers, sensors, motors, breadboards, and a wall of
          components you've probably never touched. You hand us back a machine. No hardware
          experience required — mentors roam the floor all night, and every team gets a starter kit
          that works out of the box.
        </p>
        <p>
          It's completely free. Food, parts, tools, swag — covered. You bring a laptop, an idea you
          can't let go of, and the willingness to stay up past your bedtime making something real.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 4vh, 3rem);
    max-width: 18ch;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 3rem);
    max-width: 60rem;
  }

  .about-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about-cols {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
